cat > app/views/pages/about.html.erb <<'ERB'
<%# all comments are lowercase %>

<h1 class="h3 mb-3">about this project</h1>

<p>this app uses real datasets and a fallback generator to demonstrate data collection, storage, associations, search, filtering, pagination, navigation, and simple maps.</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">datasets</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>rest countries api</strong>: country metadata (name, cca2 code, region, capital, latlng, population, area). used to populate the countries table.</li>
  <li><strong>open brewery db api</strong>: brewery metadata (name, brewery_type, address, city, state, postal_code, latitude, longitude, website_url, phone, country). used to populate the breweries table, linked to countries.</li>
  <li><strong>faker gem</strong>: fallback generator when apis are unavailable or slow, to ensure enough rows for marking.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="h5 mt-4">database structure</h2>
<ul>
  <li>countries(id, name, code, region, capital, population, area, lat, lng, timestamps)</li>
  <li>breweries(id, name, brewery_type, street, city, state, postal_code, website_url, phone, latitude, longitude, external_id, country_id, timestamps)</li>
  <li>tags(id, name, timestamps)</li>
  <li>brewery_tags(id, brewery_id, tag_id, timestamps)</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">erd (text diagram)</h2>
<pre>
country (1) -------- (many) brewery
brewery (many) --- (many) tag through brewery_tag
</pre>
<h2 class="h5 mt-4">integration plan</h2>
<ol>
  <li>seed countries from rest countries api; store name, two-letter code, and lat/lng for mapping.</li>
  <li>seed breweries from open brewery db; match to countries by name or two-letter code; assign country_id.</li>
  <li>derive tags from distinct brewery_type values and populate brewery_tags for the many-to-many link.</li>
  <li>if an api fails, the seed script generates realistic rows with faker while keeping associations valid.</li>
</ol>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">what to demo</h2>
<ol>
  <li>navigation menu on all pages</li>
  <li>breweries index with search, country filter, and pagination</li>
  <li>brewery show with conditional fields (website and phone only if present) and a map if coordinates exist</li>
  <li>countries index and country show with stats, map, and a paginated list of breweries</li>
  <li>tags index and tag show with pagination</li>
</ol>
